radiallahu anhu. He looks at the messenger. This man was intelligent.

00:40:29.750 --> 00:40:34.750
He had taken part in some wars in the past. He looks at Rasulullah sallallahu alaihi wasallam.

00:40:34.750 --> 00:40:38.750
He says, Ya Rasulullah sallallahu alaihi wasallam, you have camped the army here.

00:40:38.750 --> 00:40:42.750
This is the close water to us. There is another water further down.

00:40:42.750 --> 00:40:50.750
Is it revelation from Allah, an instruction that we cannot go against that you have made us camp here with

00:40:50.750 --> 00:40:57.750
or is it just an opinion that can be changed in the sense that could we have a say, could we suggest something?

00:40:57.750 --> 00:41:01.750
So the Prophet sallallahu alaihi wasallam says, no, it is not a must that we have to be here.

00:41:01.750 --> 00:41:05.750
We have just camped here. So he says, in that case, I have an opinion.

00:41:05.750 --> 00:41:11.750
What is your opinion? Oh, Habab, my opinion is let us go to the other water.

00:41:11.750 --> 00:41:17.750
So we will have this water as well as the other water and Quraish will have no water.

00:41:17.750 --> 00:41:19.750
So when they come in, they will have no water at all.

00:41:19.750 --> 00:41:25.750
Another thing is the soil here is not fit for our horses in case it rains.

00:41:25.750 --> 00:41:28.750
What will happen? The horses will actually slip.

00:41:28.750 --> 00:41:32.750
If we go further up there, there is a little bit of sand.

00:41:32.750 --> 00:41:38.750
If it rains or there is water and so on, we will be able to have the horses very steady on the ground.

00:41:38.750 --> 00:41:42.750
So Rasulullah sallallahu alaihi wasallam immediately agreed with this opinion

00:41:42.750 --> 00:41:46.750
and he took the entire army and told them, let's get there.

00:41:46.750 --> 00:41:48.750
And so they proceeded to the next water.

00:41:48.750 --> 00:41:51.750
And now they had control of all the water in Badr.

00:41:51.750 --> 00:41:54.750
So there was no ways that Quraish would get water.

00:41:54.750 --> 00:42:00.750
And then, subhanallah, on one hand, the eve of the battle,

00:42:00.750 --> 00:42:05.750
the mushriks are busy dancing, they're busy enjoying, they're busy drinking

00:42:05.750 --> 00:42:09.750
and they are certain that they're going to win because they know how much power they have.

00:42:09.750 --> 00:42:11.750
They don't have a doubt.

00:42:11.750 --> 00:42:15.750
Abu Jahl is convinced that tomorrow we're going to win, convinced.

00:42:15.750 --> 00:42:18.750
And they don't have a doubt. So they're really enjoying drinking so much.

00:42:18.750 --> 00:42:23.750
Now you and I know that when there is a person who has drunk so much

00:42:23.750 --> 00:42:30.750
the following morning he gets up with half an eye this way, that way, probably looking at you with one eye and so on.

00:42:30.750 --> 00:42:34.750
And he sees two, three people not realizing exactly which one is the real person

00:42:34.750 --> 00:42:36.750
and which one is just the double because of the eye.

00:42:36.750 --> 00:42:37.750
This happens.

00:42:37.750 --> 00:42:40.750
I don't know, in my part of the world they call it babalas.

00:42:40.750 --> 00:42:41.750
I don't know what they call it here.

00:42:41.750 --> 00:42:44.750
Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala protect us.

00:42:44.750 --> 00:42:47.750
So a person comes and these people were drinking.

00:42:47.750 --> 00:42:51.750
That same drink was one of the reasons of their downfall.

00:42:51.750 --> 00:42:55.750
And it was a means that Allah had chosen for their downfall.

00:42:55.750 --> 00:42:56.750
Subhanallah.

00:42:56.750 --> 00:43:00.750
And in the meantime, the Muslims, they were concerned.

00:43:00.750 --> 00:43:01.750
They were making dua.

00:43:01.750 --> 00:43:03.750
They were engaged in prayer.

00:43:03.750 --> 00:43:06.750
They were really at the mercy of Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala.

00:43:06.750 --> 00:43:09.750
Sa'd ibn Mu'adh tells Rasulullah sallallahu alayhi wa sallam,

00:43:09.750 --> 00:43:13.750
Ya Rasulallah, let us build for you a headquarters here.

00:43:13.750 --> 00:43:16.750
So they built at one place.

00:43:16.750 --> 00:43:18.750
It is known as Al-Arish.

00:43:18.750 --> 00:43:20.750
Up to today, if you go to Badr,

00:43:20.750 --> 00:43:24.750
there is a masjid built on that location known as Masjid Al-Arish.

00:43:24.750 --> 00:43:27.750
That is where the command center was.

00:43:27.750 --> 00:43:29.750
They had just built a little structure.

00:43:29.750 --> 00:43:32.750
Rasulullah sallallahu alayhi wa sallam would sit inside there.

00:43:32.750 --> 00:43:35.750
And when the war began, he came out obviously.

00:43:35.750 --> 00:43:38.750
But this was just for the time that they had camped in Badr.

00:43:38.750 --> 00:43:40.750
And they had camped for several days.

00:43:40.750 --> 00:43:43.750
Even after the battle, they camped for another three days.

00:43:43.750 --> 00:43:47.750
So that place Al-Arish was built in the meantime very quickly.

00:43:47.750 --> 00:43:50.750
They get together, they built this place beautifully, masha'Allah.

00:43:50.750 --> 00:43:54.750
And Sa'd ibn Mu'adh was standing out there with some of his men

00:43:54.750 --> 00:43:55.750
making sure no one goes in.

00:43:55.750 --> 00:43:57.750
Abu Bakr as-Siddiq radiallahu anhu

00:43:57.750 --> 00:44:01.750
and the messenger sallallahu alayhi wa sallam were in this Arish,

00:44:01.750 --> 00:44:03.750
this little command center.

00:44:03.750 --> 00:44:05.750
And in the meantime,

00:44:05.750 --> 00:44:08.750
the Muslims are given a gift by Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala.

00:44:08.750 --> 00:44:10.750
Listen to what Allah says.

00:44:10.750 --> 00:44:15.750
إِذْ يُغَشِّيكُمُ النُّعَاسَ أَمَنَةً مِنْهُ

00:44:15.750 --> 00:44:21.750
وَيُنَزِّلُ عَلَيْكُمْ مِنَ السَّمَاءِ مَآأَ

00:44:21.750 --> 00:44:24.750
لِيُطَهِّرَكُمْ بِهِ

00:44:24.750 --> 00:44:29.750
وَيُذْهِبَ عَنْكُمْ رِجَزَ الشَّيْطَانِ

00:44:29.750 --> 00:44:32.750
وَلِيَرْبِطَ عَلَى قُلُوبِكُمْ

00:44:32.750 --> 00:44:36.750
وَيُثَبِّتَ بِهِ الْأَقْدَامِ

00:44:36.750 --> 00:44:39.750
Allah says, remember the time

00:44:39.750 --> 00:44:42.750
that the yawning overtook you.

00:44:42.750 --> 00:44:44.750
They actually fell off to sleep.

00:44:44.750 --> 00:44:47.750
Imagine people are waiting, the enemy is there.

00:44:47.750 --> 00:44:48.750
Who would sleep?

00:44:48.750 --> 00:44:50.750
People would be wide awake, waiting

00:44:50.750 --> 00:44:52.750
to say the following morning we're going to fight

00:44:52.750 --> 00:44:55.750
and here you have sleep, everybody slept.

00:44:55.750 --> 00:44:58.750
The Muslims had a good sleep, mashaAllah.

00:44:58.750 --> 00:45:00.750
Allah says, we blessed you with a good sleep

00:45:00.750 --> 00:45:03.750
and above that we caused the rain to fall.

00:45:03.750 --> 00:45:05.750
So much so that the following morning

00:45:05.750 --> 00:45:07.750
the valley had water in it.

00:45:07.750 --> 00:45:08.750
What happened?

00:45:08.750 --> 00:45:12.750
That Sahabi al-Habab ibn al-Mundin, he was correct.

00:45:12.750 --> 00:45:15.750
The soil, the sand was now good enough

00:45:15.750 --> 00:45:18.750
for the horses to tread over

00:45:18.750 --> 00:45:21.750
whereas it had been quicksand the previous day.

00:45:21.750 --> 00:45:23.750
But now that it was all wet,

00:45:23.750 --> 00:45:26.750
it was beautiful because the horses could move on it

00:45:26.750 --> 00:45:28.750
and Quraysh were in a place where

00:45:28.750 --> 00:45:29.750
they suffered in the night.

00:45:29.750 --> 00:45:32.750
Their horses couldn't even move because of the water.

00:45:32.750 --> 00:45:34.750
The opposite, subhanAllah.

00:45:34.750 --> 00:45:36.750
And they didn't have water to drink

00:45:36.750 --> 00:45:38.750
and on this side it rained, subhanAllah.

00:45:38.750 --> 00:45:39.750
And this is Allah's gift.

00:45:39.750 --> 00:45:41.750
And Allah says, we sent you the water

00:45:41.750 --> 00:45:43.750
for it to be a cleansing for you

00:45:43.750 --> 00:45:46.750
and for the whispers of the devil to go.

00:45:46.750 --> 00:45:49.750
People became very very energetic

00:45:49.750 --> 00:45:51.750
and they were looking forward to the next day

00:45:51.750 --> 00:45:52.750
because of the rain.

00:45:52.750 --> 00:45:54.750
Rain freshens you up, mashaAllah.

00:45:54.750 --> 00:45:57.750
And at the same time Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala says,

00:45:57.750 --> 00:46:00.750
and in order for you to be steadfast,

00:46:00.750 --> 00:46:03.750
may Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala grant us goodness.

00:46:03.750 --> 00:46:04.750
So this was a gift

00:46:04.750 --> 00:46:07.750
that Rasulullah sallallahu alayhi wa sallam was given.

00:46:07.750 --> 00:46:08.750
Another thing,

00:46:08.750 --> 00:46:12.750
Allah showed Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wa sallam a dream.

00:46:12.750 --> 00:46:14.750
In his dream, Allah says,

00:46:14.750 --> 00:46:19.750
إذ يريكهم الله في منامك قليلا

00:46:19.750 --> 00:46:24.750
We showed their number to you in your dream as very little.

00:46:24.750 --> 00:46:28.750
So in the dream Allah showed Rasulullah sallallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:46:28.750 --> 00:46:32.750
the number of the mushriks very very little, very little.

00:46:32.750 --> 00:46:35.750
Now one might say the dreams of the Prophets are all true.

00:46:35.750 --> 00:46:38.750
So why is it that he saw them little when they were so big?

00:46:38.750 --> 00:46:39.750
No.

00:46:39.750 --> 00:46:42.750
Compared to the Iman that was on one side,

00:46:42.750 --> 00:46:44.750
they were nil on the other side.

00:46:44.750 --> 00:46:45.750
Allahu Akbar.

00:46:45.750 --> 00:46:46.750
They were nothing.

00:46:46.750 --> 00:46:47.750
So it's not the figures,

00:46:47.750 --> 00:46:49.750
it is actually the strength,

00:46:49.750 --> 00:46:53.750
the strength given by Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala due to Iman.

00:46:53.750 --> 00:46:55.750
So Allah showed him that they are very very little.

00:46:55.750 --> 00:46:56.750
Allah says,

00:46:56.750 --> 00:47:00.750
If we had showed you that they were so large in number,

00:47:00.750 --> 00:47:01.750
perhaps they would have been a dispute,

00:47:01.750 --> 00:47:05.750
perhaps you may not have wanted to fight them and so on.

00:47:05.750 --> 00:47:08.750
But Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala saved you.

00:47:08.750 --> 00:47:11.750
So this was a dream that Rasulullah sallallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:47:11.750 --> 00:47:12.750
had that eve.

00:47:12.750 --> 00:47:15.750
And then, subhanallah,

00:47:15.750 --> 00:47:16.750
on the other hand,

00:47:16.750 --> 00:47:20.750
the number of the mushriks very very little.

00:47:21.750 --> 00:47:23.750
And then, subhanallah,

00:47:23.750 --> 00:47:25.750
on the other hand,

00:47:25.750 --> 00:47:27.750
one man also saw a dream.

00:47:27.750 --> 00:47:29.750
His name was Juhaym ibn al-Salt.

00:47:29.750 --> 00:47:31.750
He was from amongst the mushriks,

00:47:31.750 --> 00:47:33.750
one of those people of Abu Jahl.

00:47:33.750 --> 00:47:34.750
He had a dream.

00:47:34.750 --> 00:47:37.750
That dream was also a sign from Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala.

00:47:37.750 --> 00:47:39.750
He dreamt that a man came to him on a horse

00:47:39.750 --> 00:47:41.750
and with a little camel of his.

00:47:41.750 --> 00:47:43.750
And he says,

00:47:43.750 --> 00:47:45.750
Such and such a person is already killed.

00:47:45.750 --> 00:47:46.750
Such a person is killed.

00:47:46.750 --> 00:47:47.750
Such a person is murdered.

00:47:47.750 --> 00:47:48.750
Such a person is murdered.

00:47:48.750 --> 00:47:49.750
Who were the names?

00:47:49.750 --> 00:47:51.750
Abu Jahl, Umayyah ibn Khalaf,

00:47:51.750 --> 00:47:52.750
Utbah ibn Rabi'ah.

00:47:52.750 --> 00:47:54.750
These people are already murdered.

00:47:54.750 --> 00:47:56.750
So this man goes to Abu Jahl

00:47:56.750 --> 00:47:57.750
and he tells him,

00:47:57.750 --> 00:47:58.750
Hey, I saw a dream.

00:47:58.750 --> 00:47:59.750
And in the dream,

00:47:59.750 --> 00:48:01.750
I saw that this man comes and tells me,

00:48:01.750 --> 00:48:03.750
You are murdered.

00:48:03.750 --> 00:48:05.750
The other one is executed.

00:48:05.750 --> 00:48:06.750
Umayyah ibn Khalaf is executed.

00:48:06.750 --> 00:48:07.750
Utbah ibn Rabi'ah.

00:48:07.750 --> 00:48:09.750
And he took the names.

00:48:09.750 --> 00:48:10.750
Abu Jahl began to laugh.

00:48:10.750 --> 00:48:11.750
Obviously half drunk.

00:48:11.750 --> 00:48:13.750
The man doesn't know what he's saying.

00:48:13.750 --> 00:48:14.750
And he starts laughing.

00:48:14.750 --> 00:48:15.750
He says, Who do you think you are?

00:48:15.750 --> 00:48:17.750
Tomorrow we will show you who's going to win.

00:48:17.750 --> 00:48:20.750
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala protect us.

00:48:20.750 --> 00:48:22.750
Wallahi, alcohol is something

00:48:22.750 --> 00:48:24.750
we should stay very, very far from.

00:48:24.750 --> 00:48:25.750
Very far.

00:48:25.750 --> 00:48:26.750
It is totally prohibited.

00:48:26.750 --> 00:48:28.750
It is known as one of the root causes

00:48:28.750 --> 00:48:30.750
of most other ill.

00:48:30.750 --> 00:48:33.750
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala safeguard us.

00:48:33.750 --> 00:48:36.750
So the following day, subhanallah,

00:48:36.750 --> 00:48:37.750
the Prophet salallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:48:37.750 --> 00:48:39.750
got the people ready.

00:48:39.750 --> 00:48:40.750
And he started advising them.

00:48:40.750 --> 00:48:42.750
He read for them verses.

00:48:42.750 --> 00:48:43.750
He warned them.

00:48:43.750 --> 00:48:45.750
He gave them lots of advice.

00:48:45.750 --> 00:48:46.750
And he told them to be disciplined.

00:48:46.750 --> 00:48:48.750
To be disciplined in war.

00:48:48.750 --> 00:48:49.750
And to listen to the instructions

00:48:49.750 --> 00:48:50.750
of the commander

00:48:50.750 --> 00:48:52.750
who was Rasulullah salallahu alayhi wa sallam.

00:48:52.750 --> 00:48:54.750
He said, We have been taught

00:48:54.750 --> 00:48:56.750
to make Sufuf.

00:48:56.750 --> 00:48:57.750
Sufuf.

00:48:57.750 --> 00:49:14.750
Allah loves those who when they are on the battlefield

00:49:14.750 --> 00:49:15.750
and they are fighting,

00:49:15.750 --> 00:49:16.750
they are in rows.

00:49:16.750 --> 00:49:18.750
Rows like the rows of Salah.

00:49:18.750 --> 00:49:20.750
Subhanallah.

00:49:20.750 --> 00:49:21.750
So there was a row.

00:49:21.750 --> 00:49:23.750
The first row was made of those

00:49:23.750 --> 00:49:26.750
who were the archers.

00:49:26.750 --> 00:49:29.750
Those who would actually use their bows and arrows,

00:49:29.750 --> 00:49:31.750
their arrows and spears to attack.

00:49:31.750 --> 00:49:32.750
And he said,

00:49:32.750 --> 00:49:34.750
We don't have that many spears.

00:49:34.750 --> 00:49:36.750
So don't waste them.

00:49:36.750 --> 00:49:38.750
And at the same time,

00:49:38.750 --> 00:49:41.750
you wait until they come right to us.

00:49:41.750 --> 00:49:43.750
When they are very close to us,

00:49:43.750 --> 00:49:44.750
then you hit them with the spears.

00:49:44.750 --> 00:49:45.750
And the others,

00:49:45.750 --> 00:49:48.750
the next row was those with swords.

00:49:48.750 --> 00:49:50.750
He said, As for you,

00:49:50.750 --> 00:49:52.750
don't remove your swords

00:49:52.750 --> 00:49:55.750
until they are right in your midst.

00:49:55.750 --> 00:49:56.750
Then you take your swords out.

00:49:56.750 --> 00:49:58.750
Subhanallah.

00:49:58.750 --> 00:50:00.750
And they didn't have the question of horsemen

00:50:00.750 --> 00:50:01.750
because there were only two.

00:50:01.750 --> 00:50:03.750
And they were told,

00:50:03.750 --> 00:50:04.750
instructed very carefully

00:50:04.750 --> 00:50:06.750
by Rasulullah salallahu alayhi wa sallam.

00:50:06.750 --> 00:50:08.750
So what had happened is,

00:50:08.750 --> 00:50:11.750
as Rasulullah salallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:50:11.750 --> 00:50:12.750
made this dua,

00:50:12.750 --> 00:50:15.750
Allah responded his dua.

00:50:15.750 --> 00:50:17.750
Nabi salallahu alayhi wa sallam says,

00:50:17.750 --> 00:50:18.750
O Allah,

00:50:18.750 --> 00:50:19.750
help us, assist us.

00:50:19.750 --> 00:50:21.750
You promised us assistance.

00:50:21.750 --> 00:50:24.750
We are asking you for help, O Allah.

00:50:24.750 --> 00:50:26.750
Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala says,

00:50:26.750 --> 00:50:32.750
إذ يوحي ربك إلى الملائكة أني معكم

00:50:32.750 --> 00:50:33.750
In fact,

00:50:33.750 --> 00:50:34.750
there is a verse slightly before that

00:50:34.750 --> 00:50:35.750
where Allah says,

00:50:35.750 --> 00:50:38.750
إذ تستغيثون ربكم

00:50:38.750 --> 00:50:47.750
فاستجاب لكم أني ممدكم بألف من الملائكة مردفين

00:50:47.750 --> 00:50:50.750
Remember when you were seeking the help of Allah

00:50:50.750 --> 00:50:52.750
and Allah responded you saying,

00:50:52.750 --> 00:50:56.750
We are sending you one thousand angels to help you.

00:50:56.750 --> 00:50:58.750
The following day,

00:50:58.750 --> 00:51:02.750
or when the battle was about to commence in fact,

00:51:02.750 --> 00:51:03.750
the verses came down.

00:51:03.750 --> 00:51:05.750
In fact, Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala told

00:51:05.750 --> 00:51:07.750
Muhammad salallahu alayhi wa sallam,

00:51:07.750 --> 00:51:08.750
We are sending you,

00:51:08.750 --> 00:51:11.750
how would you like it if we sent you three thousand angels?

00:51:11.750 --> 00:51:12.750
And then he says,

00:51:12.750 --> 00:51:15.750
We are sending you five thousand angels

00:51:15.750 --> 00:51:17.750
if you fear Allah and so on.

00:51:17.750 --> 00:51:18.750
And wallahi,

00:51:18.750 --> 00:51:20.750
if you look at Sahih al-Bukhari,

00:51:20.750 --> 00:51:21.750
you open the book,

00:51:21.750 --> 00:51:22.750
there is a baab,

00:51:22.750 --> 00:51:23.750
baab meaning a chapter.

00:51:23.750 --> 00:51:25.750
The chapter is named

00:51:25.750 --> 00:51:29.750
the chapter of the participation of the angels in the battle of Badr

00:51:29.750 --> 00:51:30.750
and ahadith,

00:51:30.750 --> 00:51:32.750
there are few ahadith that are made mention of.

00:51:32.750 --> 00:51:35.750
So the angels also took part in this battle of Badr.

00:51:35.750 --> 00:51:36.750
Now at that time,

00:51:36.750 --> 00:51:40.750
the battles used to always commence with a duel.

00:51:40.750 --> 00:51:43.750
You know, people who would have a sword fight.

00:51:43.750 --> 00:51:46.750
So three of the people of Quraysh came out.

00:51:46.750 --> 00:51:48.750
When Quraysh had come in,

00:51:48.750 --> 00:51:50.750
Quraysh walked to a specific spot.

00:51:50.750 --> 00:51:53.750
The Muslims walked to a specific spot

00:51:53.750 --> 00:51:54.750
and they were all in lines.

00:51:54.750 --> 00:51:56.750
Quraysh was haphazard.

00:51:56.750 --> 00:51:57.750
First time in the history,

00:51:57.750 --> 00:51:59.750
they are witnessing people drawing lines,

00:51:59.750 --> 00:52:00.750
you know, making lines

00:52:00.750 --> 00:52:02.750
and people all lined up.

00:52:02.750 --> 00:52:04.750
Quraysh was surprised.

00:52:04.750 --> 00:52:07.750
Rasulullah ﷺ went with his spear

00:52:07.750 --> 00:52:08.750
straightening the safs,

00:52:08.750 --> 00:52:10.750
straight like the saf of salah.

00:52:10.750 --> 00:52:12.750
The rows were made straight

00:52:12.750 --> 00:52:14.750
and the Prophet ﷺ then

00:52:14.750 --> 00:52:16.750
selected three people to go out

00:52:16.750 --> 00:52:19.750
to face the three whom Quraysh had picked up.

00:52:19.750 --> 00:52:20.750
Whom did they pick up?

00:52:20.750 --> 00:52:22.750
They picked up Utbah ibn Rabi'ah,

00:52:22.750 --> 00:52:23.750
Shaybah ibn Rabi'ah

00:52:23.750 --> 00:52:25.750
and Al-Walid ibn Utbah.

00:52:25.750 --> 00:52:26.750
Those three had come up.

00:52:26.750 --> 00:52:28.750
Al-Walid was a youngster.

00:52:28.750 --> 00:52:30.750
The other two were older people.

00:52:30.750 --> 00:52:33.750
On this side, Hamza ibn Abdul Muttalib came out

00:52:33.750 --> 00:52:37.750
and we have Ali ibn Abi Talib r.a. who came out

00:52:37.750 --> 00:52:41.750
and Ubaydah ibn Al-Harith r.a. who came out.

00:52:41.750 --> 00:52:42.750
And subhanallah,

00:52:42.750 --> 00:52:44.750
it started off with a few words

00:52:44.750 --> 00:52:45.750
and then these,

00:52:45.750 --> 00:52:47.750
the armies, the two of them watch.

00:52:47.750 --> 00:52:49.750
They wait for the duel to complete

00:52:49.750 --> 00:52:52.750
and then they all start fighting.

00:52:52.750 --> 00:52:55.750
So what happened as the duel commenced,

00:52:55.750 --> 00:52:57.750
Hamza r.a. in no time

00:52:57.750 --> 00:53:01.750
put an end to Shaybah ibn Rabi'ah.

00:53:01.750 --> 00:53:03.750
And Ali r.a. in no time

00:53:03.750 --> 00:53:05.750
executed Al-Walid.

00:53:05.750 --> 00:53:09.750
And as for Ubaydah ibn Al-Harith,

00:53:09.750 --> 00:53:12.750
Utbah ibn Rabi'ah gave him a difficult time

00:53:12.750 --> 00:53:13.750
and struck him,

00:53:13.750 --> 00:53:16.750
but he was struck as well.

00:53:16.750 --> 00:53:18.750
And then Hamza and Ali r.a. came to his assistance

00:53:18.750 --> 00:53:21.750
and this man was executed as well.

00:53:21.750 --> 00:53:23.750
Quraysh was shocked.

00:53:23.750 --> 00:53:24.750
They were shocked.

00:53:24.750 --> 00:53:28.750
Their leaders were gone, some of them.

00:53:28.750 --> 00:53:30.750
And as they were shocked,

00:53:30.750 --> 00:53:36.750
you now find that the two armies began,

00:53:36.750 --> 00:53:39.750
in fact Quraysh began to run towards the Muslims.

00:53:39.750 --> 00:53:40.750
The Muslims were just waiting

00:53:40.750 --> 00:53:41.750
exactly where they were.

00:53:41.750 --> 00:53:43.750
When they got to a specific point,

00:53:43.750 --> 00:53:45.750
they were instructed to remove their spears and arrows.

00:53:45.750 --> 00:53:46.750
They removed them.

00:53:46.750 --> 00:53:48.750
Then they were instructed to fire.

00:53:48.750 --> 00:53:49.750
When they fired,

00:53:49.750 --> 00:53:53.750
so many of Quraysh were already gone,

00:53:53.750 --> 00:53:55.750
subhanallah, just by that.

00:53:55.750 --> 00:53:56.750
And as they went,

00:53:56.750 --> 00:53:58.750
the horsemen of Quraysh began to come.

00:53:58.750 --> 00:53:59.750
They fired again.

00:53:59.750 --> 00:54:01.750
A lot of the horses dropped.

00:54:01.750 --> 00:54:04.750
And thereafter, subhanallah, the war began.

00:54:04.750 --> 00:54:08.750
And the greatest loss of the kuffar of Quraysh.

00:54:08.750 --> 00:54:09.750
It is shocking.

00:54:09.750 --> 00:54:12.750
The leaders of Quraysh, one by one,

00:54:12.750 --> 00:54:15.750
they were executed by the same people

00:54:15.750 --> 00:54:18.750
whom they had troubled and harassed over time.

00:54:18.750 --> 00:54:21.750
There are some beautiful incidents of how

00:54:21.750 --> 00:54:24.750
some young boys took part in this war

00:54:24.750 --> 00:54:27.750
and they had a very, very big impact and effect.

00:54:27.750 --> 00:54:29.750
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala grant us goodness.

00:54:29.750 --> 00:54:31.750
Insha'Allah, tomorrow we will continue.

00:54:31.750 --> 00:54:33.750
We leave you in that suspense.

00:54:33.750 --> 00:54:35.750
By the will of Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala,

00:54:35.750 --> 00:54:37.750
tomorrow we will continue with the rest of the battle.

00:54:37.750 --> 00:54:38.750
Until then, we say,

00:54:38.750 --> 00:54:41.750
wa salallahu wa sallam wa baraka ala nabina Muhammad.

00:54:41.750 --> 00:54:42.750
Subhanallah, bi hamdi.

00:54:42.750 --> 00:54:43.750
Subhanaka Allahumma bi hamdik.

00:54:43.750 --> 00:54:45.750
nashahadu alla ilaha illa anta

00:54:45.750 --> 00:54:46.750
nastaghfiruka wa natubu ilayk.

00:54:46.750 --> 00:54:50.750
Alhamdu lillahi rabbil alamin

00:54:50.750 --> 00:54:53.750
Ar-Rahman al-Rahim

00:54:53.750 --> 00:54:56.750
Maliki yawm al-deen

00:54:56.750 --> 00:54:58.750
Iyyaka na'abub
